text: The University of New Orleans offers an education for those who are full-time doers and all-time dreamers. Our campus is a place for those who know the future isn’t something you wait for...

The National Security Agency and the Department of Homeland Security have designated the University of New Orleans as a National Center of Academic Excellence in Cyber Defense Research. UNO is one of about 60 designated research centers in the country and the only one in Louisiana.

Due to a high demand for our graduates and the quality of our challenging program, we expect to continue to thrive and take our place among the best Naval Architecture and Marine Engineering programs in the world.

Where better to study jazz than New Orleans? This UNO Program of Excellence, founded in 1989 by jazz patriarch Ellis Marsalis, is celebrated for distinction in teaching, unique performance opportunities and distinguished alumni.

Our school offers one of the best known bachelors and master's degrees in Hotel, Restaurant and Tourism Administration. Our exceptional master's degree program is the only one in the state of Louisiana.
receive some form of financial assistance

has ranked UNO among the national universities whose students graduate with the lightest debt loads. Nearly 77% of our students receive some form of financial assistance every year, totaling over $41 million dollars in financial aid and scholarships.
employed within two years after graduating

90% of our students are employed two years after graduation according to Niche.com. Within the past year, UNO was also ranked tops in the state in lowest student debt and number one in Louisiana in highest early career salaries.

As a UNO student, you’ll gain a whole new perspective on New Orleans. With our deep connections and professional partnerships, you’ll experience the entrepreneurial spirit of a city that has shown the world a new standard of American reinvention. What you learn here can take you just about anywhere.
People come to New Orleans from all over the world to experience a culture that can’t be found anywhere else.
This city has grown into a hot spot for tech and innovation with Inc.com naming New Orleans “the Coolest Start-up City in America.”
Forbes.com has named New Orleans fourth in its list of America's coolest cities for 2017.
New Orleans is the perfect place to launch your career. According to the Urban Land Institute and Time Magazine, New Orleans is No. 5 on the list of the 25 Cities Where Millennials Are Moving.

If you're up to the challenge, we want you to bring that energy to our campus, along with your ideas, your perspective and your ambition. Every year when we welcome a new class, UNO takes on a slightly different personality. Because our students make this place what it is.

We share more than a name with our city: we share the culture of New Orleans, a city that never quits and has shown the world how to engineer a reinvention. Here, you will be part of a community full of people who are as determined as they are intellectually curious. And what you learn here can take you just about anywhere. Bring your ambition, and we will give you all the preparation you need to succeed.

“From the minute I arrived, there was high energy and inclusivity. Everyone, including students and faculty, made me feel as if I had a purpose here and opened up like we were family.”  ~Dalton | Major: Mathematics

The PEC is the University of New Orleans' "one-stop shop" for enrollment services. Staff at the PEC can assist students with academic advising, financial aid, admissions, registering for classes, paying fee bills, obtaining parking decals, and any other enrollment needs.

We’re excited that you want to join our community of determined and talented degree-seekers! And we’re more than ready to give you the preparation you’ll need to launch a career that’s right for you. Our only question is: Are you ready? If you are, then apply now and let’s begin your future.

Keep these dates and deadlines handy to help you stay on track.
Looking for more information? Let us know and we will keep you informed.
Immediately after you apply, you should feel completely energized and optimistic. After all, you’re on your way! But there are still things you’ll need to send us:
Your official test scores. IELTS scores may be sent via mail. All other scores (ACT, SAT, GRE, GMAT, TOEFL) should be reported electronically by the testing agency.
Your official transcripts. Send us transcripts from each and every institution you have attended. International students may also need to submit certified English translations of your transcripts.

The Application Fee. If you did not pay the application fee when you submitted your application or have been contacted by our staff regarding an unsuccessful payment, you can re-submit the payment information here.
Read up on our Residency Requirements. This is where you can find out about our on-campus residency requirements and exemptions. All the necessary paperwork is there.
Check your admission status. If you've already started the application process, log in to view your status, submit extra materials, and complete your application.
